## Component Styling

This project uses the "new-york" style variant with the "neutral" base color and CSS variables for theming, as configured in `components.json`.

## Tasteful, Semantic Usage

- Prefer shadcn primitives over bespoke elements (e.g., use `Button`, `Card`, `Badge`).
- Customize with component `variant`/`size` props first; then compose with token-based classes.
- Use Tailwind semantic tokens from `app/globals.css` (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, `rounded-md`, scale-based spacing/typography).
- Avoid raw color values, inline styles, and arbitrary sizes in component usage.
- If a design needs a new value, extend tokens centrally; don’t hardcode values in `className`.
- Keep overrides minimal and composable; prefer composition over heavy wrappers.

```tsx
// ✅ Good: variants + tokens
<Button variant="secondary" size="sm" className="rounded-md text-foreground">Action</Button>

// ❌ Avoid: raw values and ad-hoc styles
<button className="px-[18px] py-[9px] bg-[#111] text-[hsl(0,0%,98%)] rounded-[7px]">Action</button>
```
